description: From pre- (“before”) +‎ historic, q.v., similar to slightly earlier ante-historic.

adjectives.description: prehistoric (comparative more prehistoric, superlative most prehistoric)

entries.meaning: (properly) Of or relating to the epoch before written record.
examples: Was it then in a pre-historic time that the Romans wandered into these lands?

entries.meaning: (inexact or humorous) Ancient; very old, outdated, etc.
